                            <comment id="12738472" author="daijy" created="Mon, 3 Aug 2009 18:17:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also the following script produce the wrong schema:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;a = load &apos;a&apos;;&lt;br/&gt;
b = load &apos;b&apos;;&lt;br/&gt;
c = join a by $0, b by $0;&lt;br/&gt;
describe c;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;c: &lt;/p&gt;
{bytearray,bytearray}

&lt;p&gt;The correct behavior should be: If any of the input schema is unkown, the output schema is also unkown. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
